---

layout: 'base'

---

<!-- wrap -->
<div class="wrapper">
  <div class="stage"></div>
  <section class="row row-no-container carouselRow">
    <div class="center">
    <!--[if lt IE 8]>
      <p class="alert alert-info">
        You are using Internet Explorer 7 or lower. <br/>
        Please consider upgrading your browser to Internet Explorer 9 (or higher) in order to enjoy all features of this site. <br/>
        Using a different browser such as Firefox or Chrome works fine, too.
      </p>
    <![endif]-->
    </div>
    <div id="camundaCarousel" class="carousel slide visible-md visible-lg" data-interval="6500" data-pause="hover" data-wrap="true">
      <div class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="active item"> <!-- Platform -->
          <div class="center">
            <h1>Open Source BPM and Workflow with BPMN 2.0</h1>
            <p>
              <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg carousel-button" href="<%= @docUrl('download/') %>">
                Download camunda BPM 7.1 »
              </a>
            </p>
            <p class="carousel-link">
              <a href="http://docs.camunda.org/latest/">Read Documentation</a><span class="text-spacer"></span>
              <a href="<%= @docUrl('get-started/') %>">Read Getting Started</a>
            </p>
            <a href="<%= @docUrl('/features/') %>">
              <img class="carousel-image" src="<%= @docUrl('assets/img/carousel/startPage.png') %>" />
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item"> <!-- Modeler -->
          <div class="center">
            <h1>Process Modeling with BPMN 2.0</h1>
            <p>
              <a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary carousel-button" href="<%= @docUrl('download/modeler.html') %>">
                <i class="icon-download-alt icon-large icon-white"></i> Download camunda Modeler for BPMN 2.0
              </a>
            </p>
            <p class="carousel-link">
              <a href="<%= @docUrl('/features/modeler.html') %>">Features</a><span class="text-spacer"></span>
              <a href="<%= @docUrl('bpmn/tutorial.html') %>">Read BPMN 2.0 Modeling Tutorial</a>
            </p>
            <a href="<%= @docUrl('/features/modeler.html') %>">
              <img class="carousel-image" src="<%= @docUrl('assets/img/carousel/startPage-modeler.png') %>" />
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item"> <!-- Book -->
          <div class="center">
            <h1>Learn BPMN 2.0 for real</h1>
            <p>
              <a class="btn btn-lg btn-primary carousel-button" href="<%= @docUrl('bpmn/reference.html#!/reference') %>">
                Read now for free
              </a>
            </p>
            <p class="carousel-link">
              <a href="http://www.amazon.com/Real-Life-BPMN-Analyze-Automate-Processes/dp/1480034983/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1377518266&sr=8-1&keywords=bpmn+2.0" target="_blank">Order at Amazon.com</a>
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-5 col-xs-5 col-md-offset-2">
                <p>"This is a "hit the ground running" BPMN book. Within a week, I was able to use BPMN without any previous knowledge.
                  The writing is both learned and inviting, unusual combination for a translated work. I have been forced into process
                  management through circumstances at work and was not looking forward to the field. But the crisp, no nonse honest
                  writing has been a relief. It's NOT a fluff business jargon book, and technical people should find that a welcome change."<br />
                  (Amazon Customer Review)
                </p>
                <p class="carousel-paragraph">"The great thing about this book is that it goes beyond the language notation and semantics. It also provides concrete
                  guidelines on how to put BPMN into practice. Translating strategic process models to executable process models is something
                  that you typically don't find a lot of information about. The authors share their big experience in that area and that was
                  coolest part for me in this book."<br />
                  (Tom Baeyens)
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-5 col-xs-5">
                <img class="carousel-image" src="<%= @docUrl('assets/img/carousel/rl-bpmn-book.jpg') %>" />
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a class="carousel-control left" href="#camundaCarousel" data-slide="prev">‹</a>
      <a class="carousel-control right" href="#camundaCarousel" data-slide="next">›</a>
    </div>
    <div class="visible-xs visible-sm col-xs-12 col-sm-12">
      <div class="center">
        <h1>Open Source BPM and Workflow with BPMN 2.0</h1>
        <p>
          <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg carousel-button" href="<%= @docUrl('download/') %>">
            Download camunda BPM 7.1 »
          </a>
        </p>
        <p class="carousel-link">
          <a href="http://docs.camunda.org/latest/">Read Documentation</a><span class="text-spacer"></span>
          <a href="<%= @docUrl('get-started/') %>">Read Getting Started</a>
        </p>
        <a href="<%= @docUrl('/features/') %>">
          <img class="carousel-image" src="<%= @docUrl('assets/img/carousel/startPage.png') %>" />
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="row row-no-container">
    <hr class="fat" />
  </section>
  <div class="container">
    <%- @content %>
  </div>
</div>
